<TITLE> Tangail official held for 'poll offences' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Dec 28 (bdnews24.com) - Police picked up eight people, including a presiding officer, in Tangail on Sunday on alleged poll offences 12 hours ahead of the national vote scheduled to start 8am Monday. Bhuyanpur police said they were caught for "stamping official seals on the ballot papers ahead of time". The presiding officer is Shafiul Alam, headmaster of Nalsia Mamtaz High School. Tangail deputy commissioner and district returning officer Maksudur Rahman Patwary said locals seized the accused as they were stamping the ballot papers and later handed them over to police. The DC said he directed the local authorities to take punitive measures against the accused. bdnews24.co
